verbose_text: A high UbcH10 protein expression level has been reported in many human tumor types, including esophageal adenocarcinomas XREF_BIBR, anaplastic thyroid carcinomas XREF_BIBR, malignant breast carcinomas XREF_BIBR XREF_BIBR, hepatocellular carcinomas XREF_BIBR, astrocytic tumors XREF_BIBR, lung cancer XREF_BIBR, lymphoma XREF_BIBR and colorectal cancer XREF_BIBR, suggesting that UbcH10 is closely associated with tumor onset and progression.
